<subSubSection id="679A654DFFB60156ECB36856E23D0494" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="description">
<paragraph id="2F3F36C6FFB60156ECB36856E5C3045C" blockId="34.[136,1452,518,1445]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FFB60156ECB36856E73A0518" bold="true" box="[189,327,518,544]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Description</emphasis>
:—Herbs, annual, with taproot. Stems procumbent, ramified from the base, frequently into 4–5 branches up to 
<quantity id="E8789B23FFB60156ED36687AE7FD057D" box="[312,384,554,581]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="cm" value="35.0">35 cm</quantity>
long, glabrous and somewhat fleshy. Leaves opposite; stipules deeply laciniate on both node surfaces, 2.2–3.5 × 2.1–3.0 mm, non-ciliate; blade falcate, 7–12 × 
<quantity id="E8789B23FFB60156EF89681EE5940551" box="[903,1001,590,617]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.0">3–6 mm</quantity>
, base markedly asymmetrical abaxially prolonged into a conspicuous auricle, margins entire with basal auricles occasionally serrate, apex obtuse, rounded to retuse, surfaces without reddish spot, glabrous. Cyathia solitary at the bifurcation of dichasial branches and grouped together in axillary dichasial clusters on the branches of the last order, multiflorous, with 4–5 cymes of male flowers. Involucre glabrous; glands reddish, oblate-reniform, 0.09–0.10 × 
<quantity id="E8789B23FFB60156EF61688EE58705C1" box="[879,1018,734,761]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="0.45" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.4">0.4–0.5 mm</quantity>
; appendages white-greyish, 0.07–0.08 × 
<quantity id="E8789B23FFB60156EC906952E75A0425" box="[158,295,770,797]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="0.45" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.4">0.4–0.5 mm</quantity>
, margin entire or irregularly lobed. Capsules oval, deeply sulcate, 3–4 × 
<quantity id="E8789B23FFB60156E85C6952E2CC0425" box="[1106,1201,770,797]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5 mm</quantity>
, glabrous, with keeled mericarps; hypogynous disc polygonal to triangular, 
<quantity id="E8789B23FFB60156EEFA6976E5250479" box="[756,856,806,833]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 mm</quantity>
, with laciniate corners. Seeds pale grey, pyriform, apiculate, not tetrahedral, subcircular in cross section, 3 × 
<quantity id="E8789B23FFB60156EF1B691AE525045D" box="[789,856,842,869]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
, smooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2F3F36C6FFB60156ECB3693EE31804B0" blockId="34.[136,1452,518,1445]" box="[189,1381,878,905]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FFB60156ECB3693EE72804B0" bold="true" box="[189,341,878,904]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Iconography</emphasis>
:— 
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FFB60156ED79693EE4E104B0" author="Pignatti, S. &amp; Guarino, R. &amp; La Rosa, M." box="[375,668,878,904]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refId="ref32637" refString="Pignatti, S., Guarino, R. &amp; La Rosa, M. (2017) Flora d'italia, Ed. 2, 4. Edagricole, Bologna, 1178 pp." type="book" year="2017">
Pignatti 
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FFB60156EDD6693FE46D04B0" box="[472,528,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al.</emphasis>
(2017: 323)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FFB60156EEA6693EE51F04B0" author="Hegi, G." box="[680,866,878,904]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refId="ref30094" refString="Hegi, G. (1924) Illustrierte Flora von Mittel-Europa 5 (1). Verlag von J. F. Lehmann, Munchen, 674 pp." type="book" year="1924">Hegi (1924: 141</bibRefCitation>
, Fig. 1755), 
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FFB60156EFFE693EE2EC04B0" author="Clusius, C." box="[1008,1169,878,904]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refId="ref27895" refString="Clusius, C. (1601) Rariorum plantarum historia 4. Antwerp, 252 pp." type="book" year="1601">Clusius (1601</bibRefCitation>
: clxxxvii), Fig. 24.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2F3F36C6FFB60156ECB369C2E23D0494" blockId="34.[136,1452,518,1445]" box="[189,1088,914,941]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FFB60156ECB369C2E7BE0494" bold="true" box="[189,451,914,940]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Chromosome number</emphasis>
:—2n = 24 (
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FFB60156EE4569C2E5360495" author="Benedi, C. &amp; Orell, J. J." box="[587,843,914,941]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="239 - 243" refId="ref26675" refString="Benedi, C. &amp; Orell, J. J. (1992 b) Rapports 64 - 69. Mediterranean chromosome number reports. Flora Mediterranea 2: 239 - 243." type="journal article" year="1992">Benedì &amp; Orell 1992b</bibRefCitation>
); n = 12 (
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FFB60156EFBB69C2E24E0494" author="Hans, A. S." box="[949,1075,914,940]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="591 - 636" refId="ref29939" refString="Hans, A. S. (1973) Chromosomal conspectus of the Euphorbiaceae. Taxon 22: 591 - 636. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1218637" type="journal article" year="1973">Hans 1973</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="679A654DFFB60156ECB369E6E2950390" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="2F3F36C6FFB60156ECB369E6E3F904E8" blockId="34.[136,1452,518,1445]" box="[189,1412,950,977]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FFB60156ECB369E6E76104E8" bold="true" box="[189,284,950,976]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Ecology</emphasis>
:—Halophyte proper to subnitrophilous communities of sandy coastal areas (
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FFB60156E87769E6E30A04E8" author="Benedi, C. &amp; Orell, J. J." box="[1145,1399,950,976]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="9 - 55" refId="ref26618" refString="Benedi, C. &amp; Orell, J. J. (1992 a) Taxonomy of the genus Chamaesyce SF Gray (Euphorbiaceae) in the Iberian Peninsula and the Balearic Islands. Collectanea botanica 21: 9 - 55. https: // doi. org / 10.3989 / collectbot. 1992. v 21.92" type="journal article" year="1992">Benedì &amp; Orell 1992a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2F3F36C6FFB60156ECB3698AE35504CC" blockId="34.[136,1452,518,1445]" box="[189,1320,986,1013]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FFB60156ECB3698AE74704CC" bold="true" box="[189,314,986,1012]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Chorology</emphasis>
:—Native to the Mediterranean region, naturalized on the Pacific coast of North America.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2F3F36C6FFB60156ECB369AEE5350304" blockId="34.[136,1452,518,1445]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FFB60156ECB369AEE7D30320" bold="true" box="[189,430,1022,1048]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
Occurrence in 
<collectingCountry id="57977656FFB60156ED7869AEE7D30320" box="[374,430,1022,1048]" name="Italy" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Italy</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
:—Present in all Italian region, excluding landlocked ones: VDA, PIE, LOM, TAA and UMB. Recently confirmed for LIG (
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FFB60156EE116E72E5410304" author="Ottonello, M. &amp; Longo, D." box="[543,828,1058,1085]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="146 - 184" refId="ref32173" refString="Ottonello, M. &amp; Longo, D. (2018) Noterella 0215. Euphorbia peplis L. In: Alessandrini, A., Buono, V., Longo, D., Magni, C., Manni, Q. G. &amp; Nicolella, G. (Eds.) Acta Plantarum Notes 6: 146 - 184." type="journal article" year="2018">Ottonello &amp; Longo 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2F3F36C6FFB60156ECB36E16E2950390" blockId="34.[136,1452,518,1445]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FFB60156ECB36E16E7AB0358" bold="true" box="[189,470,1094,1120]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Taxonomic annotations</emphasis>
:—The name 
<taxonomicName id="E8804D45FFB60156EE786E16E5C80358" authority="Gray" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1821" box="[630,949,1094,1120]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Chamaesyce" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maritima">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FFB60156EE786E16E5090358" box="[630,884,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Chamaesyce maritima</emphasis>
Gray
</taxonomicName>
is illegitimate, as already stated by various authors (
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FFB60156ECE76E3AE7F103BC" author="Wheeler, L. C." box="[233,396,1130,1156]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="456 - 503" refId="ref35636" refString="Wheeler, L. C. (1943) The Genera of the Living Euphorbieae. The American Midland Naturalist 30: 456 - 503. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2421292" type="journal article" year="1943">Wheeler 1943</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FFB60156ED996E3AE46003BD" author="Burch, D. G." box="[407,541,1130,1157]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refId="ref27231" refString="Burch, D. G. (1965) A taxonomic revision of the genus Chamaesyce (Euphorbiaceae) in the Caribbean. PhD Thesis, University of Florida, 266 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 37694" type="book" year="1965">Burch 1965</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FFB60156EE266E3AE55E03BC" author="Benedi, C. &amp; Orell, J. J." box="[552,803,1130,1156]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="9 - 55" refId="ref26618" refString="Benedi, C. &amp; Orell, J. J. (1992 a) Taxonomy of the genus Chamaesyce SF Gray (Euphorbiaceae) in the Iberian Peninsula and the Balearic Islands. Collectanea botanica 21: 9 - 55. https: // doi. org / 10.3989 / collectbot. 1992. v 21.92" type="journal article" year="1992">
Benedì &amp; Orell 1992 
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FFB60156EF186E3AE55E03BC" author="Halford, D. A. &amp; Harris, W. K." box="[790,803,1130,1156]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="441 - 600" refId="ref29902" refString="Halford, D. A. &amp; Harris, W. K. (2012) A taxonomic revision of Euphorbia section Anisophyllum Roeper (Euphorbiaceae) in Australia. Austrobaileya 8: 441 - 600." type="journal article" year="2012">a</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, Yang 
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FFB60156EF606E3BE5DB03BC" box="[878,934,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al.</emphasis>
2012), being a superfluous name for 
<taxonomicName id="E8804D45FFB60156E9476E3BE3D603BC" box="[1353,1451,1130,1156]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Chamaesyce" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peplis">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FFB60156E9476E3BE3D603BC" box="[1353,1451,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">E. peplis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (Art. 52.1 of the ICN), and accordingly is typified automatically by its 
<typeStatus id="F03B8864FFB60156EFCF6EDFE58C0391" box="[961,1009,1167,1193]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">type</typeStatus>
(Art. 7.5 of the ICN).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="679A654DFFB60156ECB36EE2E511029C" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="2F3F36C6FFB60156ECB36EE2E511029C" blockId="34.[136,1452,518,1445]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FFB60156ECB36EE2E7F703F4" bold="true" box="[189,394,1202,1228]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Type designation</emphasis>
:—The specimen 630.18 preserved in 
<collectionCode id="4991AE03FFB60156EF336EE3E5FD03F5" box="[829,896,1203,1229]" country="United Kingdom" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15182" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15182" name="Linnean Society of London" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="Herbarium">LINN</collectionCode>
was treated by some authors (for example 
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FFB60156E9616EE2E6BE03C8" author="Khan, M. S." pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="71 - 161" refId="ref30848" refString="Khan, M. S. (1964) Taxonomic revision of Euphorbia in Turkey. Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden, Edinburgh 25: 71 - 161." type="journal article" year="1964">Khan 1964</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FFB60156ECC06E86E70403C8" author="El Hadidi, M. N." box="[206,377,1238,1264]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="83 - 100" refId="ref28151" refString="El Hadidi, M. N. (1973) The genus Euphorbia L. in Egypt I.: Section Anisophyllum Roep. Bulletin du Jardin botanique national de Belgique / Bulletin van de National Plantentuin van Belgie 43: 83 - 100. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3667563" type="journal article" year="1973">El Hadidi 1973</bibRefCitation>
) as the type of 
<taxonomicName id="E8804D45FFB60156EE2D6E87E4F803C8" box="[547,645,1238,1264]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Chamaesyce" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peplis">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FFB60156EE2D6E87E4F803C8" box="[547,645,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">E. peplis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, this specimen was collected by Kähler and reached Linnaeus after the publication of 
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FFB60156ED816EABE41E022C" box="[399,611,1274,1301]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Species Plantarum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FFB60156EE7F6EAAE483022C" author="Jarvis, C. E." box="[625,766,1274,1300]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refId="ref30681" refString="Jarvis, C. E. (2007) Order out of Chaos. Linnean Plant Names and their Types. The Linnean Society of London, London, 1016 pp." type="book" year="2007">Jarvis, 2007</bibRefCitation>
), and it is not original material. For this reason, we designate as 
<typeStatus id="F03B8864FFB60156ECAB6F4EE7710200" box="[165,268,1310,1336]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">lectotype</typeStatus>
the iconography of 
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FFB60156EDE46F4EE4EC0201" author="Clusius, C." box="[490,657,1310,1337]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refId="ref27895" refString="Clusius, C. (1601) Rariorum plantarum historia 4. Antwerp, 252 pp." type="book" year="1601">Clusius (1601)</bibRefCitation>
, that Linnaeus himself cited in the protologue, and that represents fairly well the morphology and habitus of the plant. Nevertheless, considering that the iconography does not display all the diagnostic characters (i.e. seed morphology), we here designate the specimen 630.18 preserved in 
<collectionCode id="4991AE03FFB60156E8C06F37E36C02B9" box="[1230,1297,1383,1409]" country="United Kingdom" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15182" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15182" name="Linnean Society of London" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="Herbarium">LINN</collectionCode>
as epitype, in order to provide an exsiccata material with all diagnostic features.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
